.TH LVIBE 1 "2026" "Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lvibe \- Lé Vibe launcher (managed Ollama + Code OSS editor)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lvibe
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ editor_args " ...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Same program as
.BR le\-vibe (1).
Launches the Lé Vibe session: optional product first\-run bootstrap,
starts a dedicated\-port \fBollama serve\fR, then your editor (default
\fB/usr/bin/codium\fR via \fBLE_VIBE_EDITOR\fR). On exit, stops the
managed Ollama process so GPU VRAM is released.
.PP
Open the current project in the editor:
.B lvibe \.
.PP
Product naming: Lé Vibe is not Microsoft Visual Studio Code; use Code \-
OSS / VSCodium\-class editors.
.SH OPTIONS
See
.BR le\-vibe (1).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/le\-vibe/
Configs, first\-run marker, welcome marker (\fB.welcome\-shown\fR), managed Ollama state,
\fBmodel\-decision.json\fR, \fBlock\-model.json\fR (concrete Ollama tag lock), \fBcontinue\-config.yaml\fR.
.TP
.I .lvibe/
Per\-project workspace memory \fBafter\fR consent on first open (e.g. \fBlvibe .\fR); see \fBle\-vibe\fR(1) and \fI/usr/share/doc/le\-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR le\-vibe (1),
.BR le\-vibe\-setup\-continue (1),
.BR codium (1),
.BR ollama (1).
Full docs: \fI/usr/share/doc/le-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
